Consider the system of linear equations:

\begin{equation}
\begin{aligned}
x + 2y + z &= 6 \\
2x + 4y + 2z &= 12 \\
x + 3y + 3z &= 9 + d
\end{aligned}
\end{equation}

where $d$ is a small perturbation. 

Determine the value of $d$ such that the system becomes ill-conditioned. Then, find the solution to the system using Gaussian elimination with partial pivoting.
